{"comments":"Core Submodular Function Types.\n\nA submodular function f : 2^V → ℝ₊ satisfies diminishing returns:\nfor all A ⊆ B and e ∉ B, f(A ∪ {e}) - f(A) ≥ f(B ∪ {e}) - f(B)\n\n## Oracle Model\n\nWe assume value oracle access: given S ⊆ V, return f(S).\nMarginal gain oracle: given e and S, return f(S ∪ {e}) - f(S).\n\n## Phantom Types\n\nThe SubmodularFn type encodes static guarantees via phantom types:\n- `v`: Ground set type\n- `m`: Monotonicity (Monotone or NonMonotone)\n- `κ`: Curvature bound\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show, Semigroup, Monoid)\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Types.GroundSet\n- Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Types.Classification\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"A submodular function f : 2^V → ℝ₊.\n\nPhantom types encode static guarantees:\n- `v`: Ground set type\n- `m`: Monotonicity (Monotone or NonMonotone)\n- `κ`: Curvature bound\n\nThe oracle provides access to f(S) and marginal gains.\n","info":{"arguments":[["v",null],["m",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"Monotonicity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],["κ",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"Curvature"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}]],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Function"],"SubmodularOracle"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":{"keyword":"type","kind":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Type"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"M